      <methods>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>GPS coordinates are recorded by the collaborators (if possible), and plants identified at least to species level</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>Record data is uploaded to Flora-On.pt by the collaborators, either using a webmapping interface or uploading a record table</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>Coordinates are generalized to the UTM 10x10 km grid and are made publicly available for download in both the species factsheets and as a WFS service:
http://www.flora-on.pt/wfs</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <sampling>
                <studyExtent>
                    <description>
                        <para>This dataset includes observations falling within mainland Portugal, most of which are posterior to the date the platform Flora-On was made available online (25/Feb/2012), although there is an important volume of data starting from the 1990 decade.</para>
                    </description>
                </studyExtent>
                <samplingDescription>
                    <para>A large portion of the records corresponds to non-exhaustive observations of collaborators, but there is also an important part of it that was originated from exhaustive field sampling campaigns. Plants are identified at least to species level either in the field or in the lab, and phenological state is recorded if in bloom. In general, no specimens are collected.</para>
                </samplingDescription>
            </sampling>
            <qualityControl>
                <description>
                    <para>Taxon nomenclature is fully controlled with a reference list, allowing neither spelling errors nor outdated synonyms. The reference checklist includes only the currently accepted names, which correspond to an updated version of the &quot;Checklist da Flora de Portugal (Continental, Açores e Madeira)&quot; ( http://ipt.gbif.pt/ipt/resource.do?r=alfa_checklist_florapt )
Exact GPS coordinates are stored in Flora-On.pt whenever possible, but are generalized to the UTM 10x10 km grid in this dataset.
The responsibility of species identification rests with the collaborators, most of which have expertise in plant identification. Additionally, the Editorial Board of Flora-On is committed to ensure a high reliability of uploaded data, hence checking regularly for unlikely or doubtful occurrence records, and asking collaborators to provide pictures, descriptions or specimens whenever needed. The Editorial Board estimates at least 95% of the records to be correctly identified under the most up-to-date nomenclature.</para>
                </description>
            </qualityControl>
      </methods>

